Yeah 90’s
Interesting. And you majored on theater? Also cool. How did you end up in tech?

Minor, English lit major. I was working part time in college doing tech work and when I graduated I got a job doing tech work full time over the summer planning to do it for a year or so before going back to grad school and I just never stopped
I see. What had you been planning to do?
Teaching English at a university to supplement writing
You went to a religious school didn’t you?
Sadly, yes.
One of my bigger regrets in life. I should have gone to any other school for pretty much anything else.
What did you major in?
The school was unaccredited, but I think my major was "Bible studies." I was in the ministry track, basically to become the pastor of a church.
Ah ok
So what got you out? Any specific thing or event or just a gradual shift?
I'm going to switch to off-topic.

Had a very interesting experience during games today. A player new to Commander was playing the Dragon precon and played [[Palace Siege]] and [[Frontier Siege]], choosing Dragon both times. Now that's not unusual for a dragon deck to choose Dragons for Frontier Siege, but fairly unusual for Palace Siege. As we went along he said he didn't choose Khans on either because he didn't have any Khan cards in his deck. We all looked at him for a moment before it dawned on us what he meant. We all had a good laugh (him included) when we explained how hit worked. The interesting thing is he plays Burn in Legacy and such, and just recently picked up the precon to play. It's very interesting to see things we take for granted that trip up even those not new to Magic.
